	<p>
	    We have created innovative antenna designs for GPS, satellite radio, and ISM markets.<br />
        <br />
	    We have 3 new technologies to choose from... 
	</p>
	<div id="techs">
	<ul id="techlist">

	<li><b>FilterMAX&#8482;</b><br />
        <br />
        Maxtena has created a proprietary filter technology that does not add any insertion
        loss to the signal path. The customer can define any filter shape required
        to block out of band signals without hurting the receiver's overall sensitivity.<br />
        <br />
        Imagine attenuating out of band blockers by 40dB and passing in band
        signals without any additonal loss. The customer can then add another 40dB
        of gain to the front end LNA boosting sensitivity and lowering noise figure.<br />
        <br />
        </li>

	<li><b>PolarMAX&#8482;</b><br />
        <br />
        Maxtena has a proprietary tuning technology that allows Maxtena designers to shift
        the resonant frequency of the antenna together with the center frequency of the
        narrowband matching network. This allows Maxtena designs to achieve the lowest 
	axial ratio in the industry ~0.2dB.  (Axial Ratio is a standard measure of quality of 		circularly polarized signals used by satellites.) <br />
        <br />
        </li>
	
	<li><b>RadioMAX&#8482;</b><br />
        <br />
        Maxtena has designed an enhanced version of its antennas that adds 2-3dB to
        the overall sensitivity of the receiver and protects the antenna from stray signals
        coming from the handset. These interfering signals are converted into common mode
        noise and can be easily removed by the customer's receiver. RadioMAX differential
	technology allows for integration directly to the RFIC enabling the customer to 
	have dramatically reduced Bill of Materials, lower cost, and the same performance
	without an external LNA.</li>
        </ul>
